@jiazhai A couple of notes:

 1. The Pulsar authn provider will have to be extended as in the current form it only supports a "single-step" authentication (and not multiple interactions between client and server). BK authn plugin is already fine.
 2. It might be worthwhile to consider implementing Kerberos on top of SASL wrapper

@narkedboy with a failover subscription, having a unique active consumer on a given partition, is guaranteed at the broker level and I am not aware of any issues in that mechanism. 

What you also might be seeing is that some the failover is being triggered when you start the consumer as the assignments are re-balanced. 

When the rebalance/failover occurs, the broker will switch the active consumer and will re-send all the unacknowledged messages to the new active consumer.

